<TITLE> Tk 10 bln proposed for ultra poor </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 10 (bdnews24.com)--The finance minister has proposed a 15 percent cut in money available for employment generation schemes of the hard core poor. The proposed allocation stands at Tk 10 billion for the 2010-11 fiscal. In his budget speech, AMA Muhith said on Thursday that Tk 11 billion was allocated in the current 2009-10 fiscal for the programme titled Employment Generation for the Hard Core Poor. In the first phase, employment was generated for about 6, 00,000 people in 16 districts, he said. The second phase will create opportunities for about 17,00,000 people in 64 districts across the country. The proposed budget will create employment for 40 percent youths. The next fiscal will generate 158 crore work days, which is 28 crore work days more than the current fiscal, he added
